Abia Warriors Goalkeeper Uche Okafor has joined his team in advocating for safety during this period.
The Nigerian goalkeeper while speaking in a short video posted in the club’s YouTube channel https://bit.ly/2U92RKk called  for safety in the midst of the fight against the coronavirus pandemic that has affected the entire World.
According to the former golden eaglets shot-stopper, the virus is real and therefore people must ensure they are doing alright.
“Coronavirus is real, please stay safe’ he said.
The former flying eagles Star who was training share his campaign while adhering to stay at home order.
















			
